1
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:52,154
My dear children.

2
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:57,951
It is now better than several years
since I moved to New York

3
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:01,121
and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.

4
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:06,501
I hope you will come to this
ceremony of Papal honors,

5
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,087
given for my charitable work.

6
00:02:11,882 --> 00:02:13,884
The only wealth
in this world is children.

7
00:02:15,427 --> 00:02:17,512
More than all the money
and power on earth,

8
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:20,390
you are my treasure.

9
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:24,436
Anthony and Mary,

10
00:02:25,604 --> 00:02:27,939
although I entrusted your education
to your mother

11
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:29,232
for your own best interest,

12
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:35,822
I look forward to seeing you, and to
a new period of harmony in our lives.

13
00:02:37,908 --> 00:02:41,912
Perhaps you might prevail upon your
mother to come to this celebration,

14
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:47,668
and that from time to time, we can all
see each other at family functions.

15
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:53,423
Anyway, I remain your loving father.

16
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:25,664
Hail Mary, full of grace...

17
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,753
...blessed art Thou amongst women...

18
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:35,090
...and blessed is the fruit
of Thy womb, Jesus.

19
00:03:37,384 --> 00:03:41,096
Holy Mary, mother of God,
pray for us sinners...

20
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:12,419
Almighty God, bless the insignia
of Saint Sebastian the martyr,

21
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,546
that it may contribute

22
00:04:15,213 --> 00:04:18,633
to the sacredness of him
to whom it is given.

23
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:35,192
Do you, Michael,
promise to be faithful

24
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:37,944
to the noble purposes of this Order,

25
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:43,575
to have a special care for the poor,
the needy and those who are ill?

26
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,160
I do so promise.

27
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,720
May the blessing of Almighty God,

28
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:08,892
Father, Son and Holy Spirit

29
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:14,481
descend upon you
and remain with you forever.

30
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:50,702
Vincent, our name is not on the list.

31
00:06:53,788 --> 00:06:57,417
Write it in. Mancini. M-A-N-C-I-N-I.

32
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:01,921
- Problem?
- My name isn't on the list.

33
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:06,635
- Then you have to leave immediately.
- You want to dance with me?

34
00:07:06,885 --> 00:07:10,013
Joe, it's Vinnie.
These are our guests.

35
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,182
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, sir.

36
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:13,933
Welcome to the party.

37
00:08:07,696 --> 00:08:11,950
- It's good to see you.
- Good to see you. This is my husband.

38
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,660
- Sit down.
- My son, Anthony.

39
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:20,291
The Order of Saint Sebastian is one of
the highest honors the Church awards.

40
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:23,002
It was first granted by Pope...

41
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:26,089
What about Mr. Corleone's connections
with gambling?

42
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:28,341
The press kits have...

43
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,885
What about his involvement
with the underworld?

44
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,137
Cut the crap.

45
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:35,598
The Pope, the Holy Father himself,

46
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:40,770
has today blessed Michael Corleone.
Do you know better than the Pope?

47
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,524
Vincent! She loves you.

48
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:45,900
Yeah?

49
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:51,906
I love you too.

50
00:08:58,163 --> 00:09:00,749
Hi, Vincent. I remember you.

51
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:06,796
- From where?
- The last party we were at together.

52
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:10,008
- Did you come to the club?
- No, it was a wedding.

53
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:14,971
I was eight and you were 15.

54
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:19,100
I had many girlfriends when I was 15.

55
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:21,394
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially them.

56
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:24,814
Where's Mary?

57
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:30,111
Would somebody please hail Mary?
Excuse me, Your Excellency.

58
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:35,033
You haven't kissed me hello yet.
Relatives always kiss.

59
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:38,161
- Now we're related?
- I'm your little cousin.

60
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:49,506
- Who's your father?
- I'll give you a hint.

61
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:52,175
He's Italian.

62
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:55,678
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

63
00:09:56,429 --> 00:10:00,308
Remember to keep your voice low.

64
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:03,019
And smile. Don't forget to smile.

65
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:27,168
The honorary chairman of
the Vito Corleone Foundation,

66
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:29,796
my daughter, Mary Corleone.

67
00:10:39,931 --> 00:10:41,099
Thanks.

68
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:47,313
I think I inherited my father's love
for speechmaking. Here it goes.

69
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:53,444
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps
the poor in every country,

70
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:57,740
gives grants to artists,
funds medical research,

71
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:02,412
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

72
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,081
Archbishop Gilday,

73
00:11:05,874 --> 00:11:10,169
here is 100 million dollars
for the poor of Sicily,

74
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:12,088
in the name of Vito Corleone.

75
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:14,716
Don't spend it all in one place.

76
00:11:32,984 --> 00:11:37,238
Mary, I'm so proud of you.

77
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:46,497
Michael...

78
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:49,417
You've done a wonderful thing
for Sicily.

79
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:53,922
Let's hope that the money gets
to the people who need it.

80
00:11:54,589 --> 00:11:55,715
Amen.

81
00:11:56,132 --> 00:12:00,929
...the most important part:
Johnny Fontane!

82
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:12,941
Thank you very much.
I'm happy to be here.

83
00:12:13,024 --> 00:12:15,485
I would like you to join me
in honoring

84
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:18,196
Commendatore Michael Corleone.

85
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:25,828
I have something special
for our godfather.

86
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:30,625
I happen to know his favorite song.
Michael, where are you going?

87
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:33,920
I'm off to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

88
00:12:36,047 --> 00:12:38,466
Your favorite song, "Salsiccia's Own".

89
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:40,885
I'm having a salsiccia sandwich.
I'll be back.

90
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:17,672
Hello, Kay.

91
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,810
Congratulations, Michael.
That's quite an honor.

92
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:33,521
But a little expensive,
wouldn't you say?

93
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:39,694
- Cake?
- No, thank you.

94
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:56,961
- It's been a long time, hasn't it?
- Yeah.

95
00:13:57,128 --> 00:13:58,713
- Eight years.
- Yeah.

96
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:01,424
You look wonderful.

97
00:14:05,303 --> 00:14:07,430
Your son has something
he wants to talk to you about.

98
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,223
I came here for him.

99
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:50,098
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- He wants his life to be in music.

100
00:14:52,183 --> 00:14:55,978
Music is great, I love music.
But he should finish what he started.

101
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:57,605
Anthony...

102
00:14:58,523 --> 00:15:00,650
- I'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

103
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:03,111
- Professional singer?
- Yes.

104
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:06,739
What happens if you fail?

105
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:10,034
- I won't fail.
- Men always believe that.

106
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:14,372
A law degree is like taking
out insurance.

107
00:15:15,373 --> 00:15:18,751
- After that you can work for me...
- I will never work for you.

108
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,046
I have bad memories.

109
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:26,592
Every family has bad memories.

110
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:32,098
I'll always be your son,

111
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:34,600
but won't have anything to do
with your business.

112
00:15:37,562 --> 00:15:40,773
Anthony... finish the law degree.

113
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:43,693
No.

114
00:16:01,169 --> 00:16:05,214
Well, that he got from you. That "no".

115
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:12,930
- You could've helped me convince him.
- Convince him of what?

116
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:14,932
Of what?

117
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:20,730
He throws his life away.
He throws greatness away.

118
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:22,899
This is greatness?

119
00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:28,738
Now that you're so respectable,
you're more dangerous than ever.

120
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:33,367
I preferred you when you were
just a common Mafia hood.

121
00:16:34,869 --> 00:16:36,037
Okay.

122
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:40,499
- Can we talk common sense here?
- All right.

123
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:49,133
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

124
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:59,477
- What did you come here for?
- To protect my son.

125
00:17:00,186 --> 00:17:04,857
Not to see you disguised by your
church. That was a shameful ceremony.

126
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,656
I spent my life protecting my son.

127
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:16,285
I spent my life protecting my family!

128
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:17,954
Let's be reasonable, okay?

129
00:17:19,789 --> 00:17:23,876
That's your big thing, isn't it,
Michael? Reason,

130
00:17:25,253 --> 00:17:28,839
- backed up by murder.
- God.

131
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:33,177
- You hate me. You hate me.
- No.

132
00:17:34,095 --> 00:17:35,304
I don't hate you.

133
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:38,641
I dread you.

134
00:17:43,104 --> 00:17:44,480
I did what I could, Kay,

135
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:49,068
to protect all of you
from the horrors of this world.

136
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,113
But you became my horror.

137
00:18:02,665 --> 00:18:05,918
The children still love you, though.
Especially Mary.

138
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:10,214
That's something.

139
00:18:13,301 --> 00:18:16,804
We can build on that. For their sake,

140
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:21,934
let's try.

141
00:18:22,852 --> 00:18:27,815
Only if you let Tony go free
to have his own life, away from you.

142
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:36,824
I'll let Tony go.

143
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:41,120
Thank you.

144
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:17,782
- Hi.
- Hi.

145
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:24,830
You could hurt somebody with those.
Let me show you around.

146
00:19:25,456 --> 00:19:27,208
Can you get me an interview
with Corleone?

147
00:19:27,917 --> 00:19:30,378
No. I'm a relative,
but I can't do that.

148
00:19:30,753 --> 00:19:32,088
What else can I do for you?

149
00:19:33,756 --> 00:19:35,800
- Handsome, but useless.
- Yeah?

150
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,886
- That's okay, I'll gamble.
- Do you like to gamble?

151
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:43,265
Let's go to Atlantic City.
I'll show you how to gamble.

152
00:19:43,516 --> 00:19:45,935
How do I know what numbers to bet?

153
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,895
Do I look like a guy who's gonna lose?

154
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:49,897
Well...

155
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:53,776
Spooky-looking guy there.

156
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:59,698
- What's a guy like that doing here?
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

157
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,784
- You know him?
- Yeah, I do.

158
00:20:03,119 --> 00:20:07,081
His name is Anthony Squigilaro.
They call him "The Ant".

159
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,875
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

160
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:18,968
Two seconds... Thank you for your
contribution to the swimming-pool.

161
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:23,514
We need your help on Sam Wallace's
candidacy for judgeship.

162
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:25,599
- We can always use a good judge.
- Thanks.

163
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,351
Andrew!

164
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:31,814
My godson Andrew Hagen.
My brother Tom's eldest boy.

165
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:36,485
He's been assistant to Bishop Breelan
for three years.

166
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:40,531
- Hopes to be assigned to the Vatican.
- Rome needs fine young priests.

167
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:43,742
His mother Teresa Hagen,
Bishop Gilday.

168
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:45,953
Honored to meet you.

169
00:20:46,537 --> 00:20:49,039
Mr. Corleone. Hi. Grace Hamilton.

170
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:54,837
Vincent Mancini promised to tell you
about me. That maybe you'd see me.

171
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:58,549
- Did Vincent Mancini call about her?
- No.

172
00:20:59,008 --> 00:21:01,802
You promised to stay out there,

173
00:21:01,886 --> 00:21:03,262
- twice.
- I know.

174
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:08,350
Joey Zasa showed up.
He's waiting in the lobby.

175
00:21:08,476 --> 00:21:11,937
He wants to personally
congratulate you. Show his respect.

176
00:21:12,855 --> 00:21:17,443
- Do I have to see him?
- He says you're his patron.

177
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:23,157
Hey, Vinnie!

178
00:21:24,158 --> 00:21:25,784
- Who's your favorite aunt?
- You are.

179
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:31,916
Today I'll talk to Michael
about your little problem.

180
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:36,420
If you'd warned me,
I would have worn a better suit.

181
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:41,091
The Meucci Association has elected you

182
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:43,719
Italian-American Man of the Year.

183
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:47,264
Meucci...

184
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:51,810
Who's Meucci?

185
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:59,151
The Italian-American who invented
the telephone, one year before Bell.

186
00:22:02,947 --> 00:22:05,908
And this is the reason
you've come today?

187
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:14,458
I...

188
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:20,047
I've got a stone in my shoe.

189
00:22:21,549 --> 00:22:23,801
A two-bit punk who works for me.

190
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:28,097
The one who thinks
he's related to you.

191
00:22:30,683 --> 00:22:31,850
A bastard.

192
00:22:35,813 --> 00:22:40,317
He's here. Vincent Mancini.
He's at the party.

193
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:45,155
Bring him in.

194
00:22:46,657 --> 00:22:49,034
I think it's good that we talk.

195
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:51,829
No, grazie.

196
00:22:53,831 --> 00:22:55,833
I have a problem...

197
00:22:56,333 --> 00:23:02,673
...and I want to find out if it is
my problem or your problem.

198
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:07,845
Your business is your business. I have
no interests or percentages from it.

199
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:12,349
Good. Then it's my problem.

200
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:21,108
Michael, you know Vincent Mancini.
Sonny's boy.

201
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:26,238
- How are you, Mr. Corleone?
- How are you?

202
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:30,117
- Good. How are you? Good party.
- You like it?

203
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:33,454
- Yes, I had to sneak in.
- You're dressed for it.

204
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:42,046
So, what's the trouble
between you and Mr. Joe Zasa?

205
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:48,719
- Just trouble. I'll take care of it.
- That's foolish of you.

206
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:53,724
Foolish of me? It's a little foolish
of this guy, don't you think? Right?

207
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:58,646
- Right?
- Temper like his father...

208
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:00,689
Vincent...

209
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:07,905
Mr. Joe Zasa now owns what used to
be the Corleone business in New York.

210
00:24:08,364 --> 00:24:12,242
Out of kindness, he gave you
a job in his family.

211
00:24:12,326 --> 00:24:15,162
You took it against my advice.

212
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:20,417
I offered you something better in the
legitimate world. You turned me down.

213
00:24:20,501 --> 00:24:25,422
Now you both come to me with this bad
blood. What do you expect me to do?

214
00:24:27,591 --> 00:24:28,967
- Am I a gangster?
- No...

215
00:24:29,051 --> 00:24:33,889
That was Papa's neighborhood.
Zasa runs it like a disgrace!

216
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:37,810
- That's the past, Connie.
- I earned that territory.

217
00:24:38,394 --> 00:24:41,814
The Commission gave it to me
and you approved.

218
00:24:42,106 --> 00:24:43,190
Yes.

219
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:47,986
I came for the party, not to ask
for help. I could kill this bastard.

220
00:24:48,070 --> 00:24:49,655
So kill him.

221
00:24:51,073 --> 00:24:54,076
What does all this have to do with me?

222
00:24:54,284 --> 00:24:59,581
Well, he goes behind your back,
saying "Fuck Michael Corleone".

223
00:24:59,665 --> 00:25:02,167
Say it to his face, one time!

224
00:25:03,877 --> 00:25:08,882
Mr. Corleone, all bastards are liars.
Shakespeare wrote poems about it.

225
00:25:08,966 --> 00:25:12,010
What am I going to do with this guy?

226
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:22,938
Joey, if there's some guy
running around this city,

227
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:25,816
saying, "Fuck Michael Corleone"...

228
00:25:27,109 --> 00:25:30,404
...what do we do
with a piece of shit like that?

229
00:25:32,823 --> 00:25:34,867
He's a fucking dog.

230
00:25:41,999 --> 00:25:45,502
Yes, it's true.
If anyone would say such a thing,

231
00:25:45,586 --> 00:25:48,839
they would not be a friend,
they would be a dog.

232
00:25:55,179 --> 00:26:01,393
- My interests don't conflict with his.
- You don't know how much they do.

233
00:26:01,477 --> 00:26:03,020
Quiet, Vincent.

234
00:26:03,145 --> 00:26:05,189
He needs your support!

235
00:26:05,272 --> 00:26:07,983
Don't let me work for this guy,
let me work for you.

236
00:26:08,066 --> 00:26:14,114
As what? Tough guy? I don't need
tough guys. I need more lawyers.

237
00:26:17,493 --> 00:26:22,414
Since we have no conflicts or debts,
I accept your tribute.

238
00:26:22,498 --> 00:26:23,999
I wish you well.

239
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:29,963
Vincent, make your peace
with Mr. Joe Zasa. Go on.

240
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,267
Bastardo...

241
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:51,068
Vinnie, what's the matter with you?

242
00:26:51,151 --> 00:26:53,320
Get him out of here.

243
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:56,782
Jesus Christ...

244
00:26:57,950 --> 00:27:00,077
I told Connie
this wasn't the right time.

245
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,161
Close it.

246
00:27:01,245 --> 00:27:05,040
I know you're into Wall Street,
but you're still the final word.

247
00:27:05,123 --> 00:27:08,043
I want to protect you from these guys.
Your lawyers can't.

248
00:27:08,126 --> 00:27:10,921
- But you can?
- Yeah, I can do that.

249
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:14,383
Why should I be afraid of Zasa?

250
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:17,928
You stop him from rising
in the Commission.

251
00:27:18,011 --> 00:27:21,223
I say we make him dead.
Give me the order, I'll do it.

252
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:23,016
- You'll do it?
- Yeah.

253
00:27:27,688 --> 00:27:32,359
Maybe you should come with me
for a few weeks. See what happens.

254
00:27:32,943 --> 00:27:35,070
- Okay.
- See if you learn.

255
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:39,199
And we'll talk about your future.

256
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:42,744
I won't let you down.

257
00:27:49,543 --> 00:27:51,128
It's about ready.

258
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:58,510
So, what happened?

259
00:27:58,594 --> 00:27:59,887
What happened?

260
00:27:59,970 --> 00:28:03,140
If I'm in a room with Zasa,
what happens? I bit his ear off.

261
00:28:03,223 --> 00:28:05,559
Here we go. Watch the card.

262
00:28:08,312 --> 00:28:09,813
Hold it!

263
00:28:12,149 --> 00:28:13,859
- Vincent...
- Yeah.

264
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:16,028
Take the picture with us.

265
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:25,078
Nice jacket.

266
00:28:27,164 --> 00:28:29,583
Closer to the center, sir.

267
00:28:53,857 --> 00:28:58,320
Godfather, this is the cake for you
and your family from Enzo the baker.

268
00:28:59,696 --> 00:29:01,615
Do you want to do it?

269
00:29:47,744 --> 00:29:50,998
Cent'anni! Cent'anni!

270
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:53,351
- Vincent?
- What do you want, sweetheart?

271
00:30:55,771 --> 00:30:57,355
Do you love me?

272
00:30:58,899 --> 00:31:01,401
- Come on, go to bed.
- Come on, say it.

273
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:05,322
I love you.

274
00:31:05,947 --> 00:31:07,866
I love you, too.

275
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:12,162
You've got a cat?

276
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:21,797
Go get us some water, I'm thirsty.
Come on.

277
00:31:22,756 --> 00:31:24,341
Come on.

278
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,351
Well, I guess I know my place.

279
00:31:35,227 --> 00:31:38,271
I can't believe
I'm actually doing this.

280
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:42,609
"Get me water, bake me a cake"...
What happened to "please"?

281
00:32:30,282 --> 00:32:33,076
Good boy, Sackface. Go for a walk.

282
00:32:42,335 --> 00:32:45,422
- Let her go.
- Cut her throat, man.

283
00:32:48,091 --> 00:32:51,052
- What did you say?
- Cut her fucking throat.

284
00:32:54,222 --> 00:32:55,223
Okay, chief...

285
00:32:55,307 --> 00:32:57,267
Drop your gun or he'll cut her throat.

286
00:32:57,350 --> 00:33:01,688
I hardly know her, so cut her.
What the fuck do I care?

287
00:33:03,648 --> 00:33:07,235
You've got no choice. She'll be dead.

288
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:11,323
If you do, I'll kill you both.
Give up that knife, I'll let you go.

289
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:14,117
Cut her throat! Right now!

290
00:33:14,201 --> 00:33:16,828
I'll do something
that'll convince you.

291
00:33:16,912 --> 00:33:20,165
Don't get frightened. Just watch me.

292
00:33:25,295 --> 00:33:26,755
Shit!

293
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:31,259
Drop the knife. Drop it!

294
00:33:31,343 --> 00:33:33,345
Good boy.

295
00:33:33,428 --> 00:33:38,225
Sit down, I want to talk to you.
It was a wise choice. Sit down.

296
00:33:38,308 --> 00:33:39,768
Lose the mask.

297
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:45,482
Relax, have a smoke. You smoke?

298
00:33:48,401 --> 00:33:50,862
Whose idea was this? Who sent you?

299
00:33:51,529 --> 00:33:53,240
Tell me who sent you.

300
00:33:56,785 --> 00:33:59,579
- No one.
- Did you take a look at this guy?

301
00:33:59,663 --> 00:34:01,790
- Yeah.
- Who sent you?

302
00:34:04,542 --> 00:34:06,836
It was Joey Zasa.

303
00:34:21,518 --> 00:34:23,061
Are you okay?

304
00:34:26,314 --> 00:34:29,567
- You were going to let them kill me!
- No, I wasn't...

305
00:34:29,651 --> 00:34:32,028
You pig! You sick fuck!

306
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:37,784
You wanted gambling. That's gambling.
Call the police.

307
00:34:42,706 --> 00:34:46,209
- You killed the other guy too?
- He went for my gun.

308
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:50,130
It was self-defense.
Go ahead, call the police.

309
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:53,466
- No, no...
- I'm taking pictures.

310
00:34:53,550 --> 00:34:55,093
No pictures.

311
00:34:56,970 --> 00:34:58,263
You had a gun!

312
00:34:58,555 --> 00:35:03,435
They only had a knife. You could have
handed them over to the police.

313
00:35:04,477 --> 00:35:07,564
Zasa sent them.
I just sent him a message.

314
00:35:08,565 --> 00:35:13,778
- Now he has to send you one back.
- Zasa is going to send me one back?

315
00:35:13,862 --> 00:35:16,698
He did the right thing.
He got Zasa's name!

316
00:35:16,781 --> 00:35:20,577
What has Joey Zasa to do
with anything? Joey Zasa is a pazzo.

317
00:35:24,414 --> 00:35:26,624
All right. You are what you are.

318
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:30,503
It's your nature. Stay close to me.

319
00:35:30,587 --> 00:35:34,466
Don't do anything. Keep your mouth
shut and your eyes open.

320
00:35:34,549 --> 00:35:37,469
- And you do what I tell you.
- I understand.

321
00:35:37,844 --> 00:35:40,972
- I have problems with the Commission.
- I know.

322
00:35:41,056 --> 00:35:45,810
- You don't make them easier.
- It wasn't my idea that this happened.

323
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:49,230
- Get out of here.
- Michael...

324
00:35:49,856 --> 00:35:51,107
Yes?

325
00:35:52,984 --> 00:35:56,571
- Now they'll fear you.
- Maybe they should fear you.

326
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:04,579
- B.J., what's up?
- The Archbishop just called back.

327
00:36:10,627 --> 00:36:12,337
Don Corleone,

328
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:18,635
I need your help.
And not just to light a little candle.

329
00:36:20,762 --> 00:36:27,310
My gift was to be able to persuade
people to give to the Holy Church.

330
00:36:28,478 --> 00:36:32,982
Then Rome decides to put me
in charge of the Vatican Bank...

331
00:36:35,276 --> 00:36:38,071
...but I was never a true banker.

332
00:36:41,241 --> 00:36:45,412
Mea culpa. I trusted my friends.

333
00:36:46,621 --> 00:36:48,623
Friendship and money...

334
00:36:49,749 --> 00:36:51,584
Oil and water...

335
00:36:51,668 --> 00:36:53,002
Indeed.

336
00:36:53,545 --> 00:37:00,427
But these "friends" used the good name
of the Church to feed their greed.

337
00:37:01,553 --> 00:37:03,596
If money was lost...

338
00:37:05,306 --> 00:37:07,183
...then I am to blame.

339
00:37:09,561 --> 00:37:14,232
If only prayer could pay off
our 700 million dollar deficit.

340
00:37:16,443 --> 00:37:18,653
769 million...

341
00:37:24,576 --> 00:37:29,789
The Church owns 25 percent
of a large corporation. Immobiliare.

342
00:37:30,748 --> 00:37:32,625
You know the one I mean?

343
00:37:32,709 --> 00:37:37,380
Largest landlord on Earth.
Real estate worth six billion dollars.

344
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:41,634
That's true.

345
00:37:42,343 --> 00:37:45,805
And the Vatican vote
is necessary for control.

346
00:37:48,725 --> 00:37:51,269
No, you're mistaken.

347
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:56,274
This isn't a question of one person
deciding. One deciding vote.

348
00:37:56,357 --> 00:38:02,155
This is like any other company.
We have directors and very old rules.

349
00:38:03,198 --> 00:38:07,160
The Pope himself
would have to approve you.

350
00:38:12,207 --> 00:38:14,125
We've sold the casinos.

351
00:38:15,835 --> 00:38:18,671
All businesses having to do
with gambling.

352
00:38:19,839 --> 00:38:25,553
We have no interests or investments
in anything illegitimate.

353
00:38:28,723 --> 00:38:30,767
The Corleones are prepared to deposit

354
00:38:30,850 --> 00:38:33,228
500 million dollars
in the Vatican Bank

355
00:38:33,311 --> 00:38:36,981
when Mr. Corleone receives majority
control of Immobiliare.

356
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:41,986
Immobiliare could be something new.
A European conglomerate.

357
00:38:43,821 --> 00:38:47,659
Few families have control
of such a company.

358
00:38:50,828 --> 00:38:53,373
It seems that, in today's world,

359
00:38:53,998 --> 00:38:58,253
the power to absolve debt is greater
than the power of forgiveness.

360
00:39:00,547 --> 00:39:02,382
600 million dollars.

361
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:10,515
Don't overestimate
the power of forgiveness.

362
00:39:12,725 --> 00:39:14,727
Don Corleone,

363
00:39:14,811 --> 00:39:17,814
this deal with Immobiliare
can make you

364
00:39:17,897 --> 00:39:19,899
one of the richest men in the world.

365
00:39:19,983 --> 00:39:23,278
Your whole past history,
and the history of your family,

366
00:39:23,903 --> 00:39:25,863
would be washed away.

367
00:39:29,576 --> 00:39:31,119
600 million.

368
00:39:49,470 --> 00:39:54,017
The motion under discussion
relates to Corleone Group's proposal

369
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:57,478
to acquire 100,000,000 newly issued
Class A voting shares.

370
00:40:01,733 --> 00:40:07,488
...Corleone capital invested directly
into International Immobiliare,

371
00:40:08,281 --> 00:40:12,452
an old and respected
European company.

372
00:40:12,535 --> 00:40:18,583
Mr. Corleone has an ambitious program
to expand this real estate company

373
00:40:18,666 --> 00:40:21,669
into an international conglomerate...

374
00:40:24,756 --> 00:40:30,553
...by Eastern techniques of efficiency
and focus and unlimited...

375
00:40:30,637 --> 00:40:32,722
Mr. Corleone, excuse me.

376
00:40:33,139 --> 00:40:36,601
Didn't you recently deposit
200 million in the Vatican Bank,

377
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:40,063
which is affiliated with Immobiliare?

378
00:40:40,146 --> 00:40:41,689
True. Why not?

379
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:48,154
Wasn't there any questioning about
the timing on this particular deposit?

380
00:40:48,237 --> 00:40:50,490
Mr. Chairman, if I may?

381
00:40:52,158 --> 00:40:56,746
The Vito Andolini Corleone Foundation,
of which Mary Corleone is chairman,

382
00:40:56,829 --> 00:41:00,208
has made an endowment
of 100 million dollars.

383
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:02,543
The money comes from his own family

384
00:41:02,627 --> 00:41:04,837
and will be
administered by the Vatican.

385
00:41:04,921 --> 00:41:07,382
Does that answer your question?

386
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:10,218
I have always believed that

387
00:41:10,301 --> 00:41:14,097
helping your fellow man
is profitable in every sense,

388
00:41:14,180 --> 00:41:16,349
personally and bottom line.

389
00:41:17,016 --> 00:41:22,814
My fellow shareholders, if Europe
and America can learn to co-operate,

390
00:41:22,897 --> 00:41:27,110
if we can learn to pool our wealth,
share our markets,

391
00:41:27,193 --> 00:41:31,989
we can defeat any competition
anywhere in the world.

392
00:41:32,615 --> 00:41:35,368
Thank you for your time.

393
00:41:35,451 --> 00:41:40,081
I hope that you will look favorably
on my proposal. Thank you.

394
00:41:46,129 --> 00:41:48,506
Let me have this microphone here.

395
00:41:48,589 --> 00:41:52,093
Will we let a criminal
run our company?

396
00:41:52,176 --> 00:41:54,470
He's got the map of Sicily
on his face!

397
00:41:54,554 --> 00:41:55,847
Order!

398
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:58,349
He's either a Catholic or a mafioso...

399
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:04,731
The Hamilton Investors Group
cannot support this proposal.

400
00:42:06,065 --> 00:42:07,066
Your Excellency...

401
00:42:08,860 --> 00:42:10,319
Mr. Chairman...

402
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:16,576
...the Vatican Bank feels
that International Immobiliare...

403
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:23,124
...will be safe.
In Mr. Corleone's hands.

404
00:42:23,332 --> 00:42:26,294
...subject to audit
and final ratification,

405
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,254
which must take place in Rome.

406
00:42:28,337 --> 00:42:31,799
Please join me in welcoming
Mr. Michael Corleone.

407
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:52,195
Go in the other car.
I'll ride with Michael.

408
00:42:52,778 --> 00:42:54,572
Go, go, go.

409
00:43:08,503 --> 00:43:13,799
As your family's oldest friend, I'm
always chosen to bring you messages.

410
00:43:16,552 --> 00:43:18,763
Tell me, Don Altobello.

411
00:43:21,474 --> 00:43:26,270
Your old partners are grateful for
the money you made them.

412
00:43:26,354 --> 00:43:28,105
They worship you...

413
00:43:28,814 --> 00:43:34,862
...but their hearts are broken,
because they think you abandoned them.

414
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:42,078
They want to share your deal
on Immobiliare, to be a family again.

415
00:43:42,161 --> 00:43:44,455
It can purify their money.

416
00:43:46,874 --> 00:43:48,543
This I cannot do.

417
00:43:51,462 --> 00:43:54,465
Immobiliare must be legitimate.

418
00:43:56,759 --> 00:43:58,094
I know.

419
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:01,180
But they're unhappy.

420
00:44:03,349 --> 00:44:04,475
And you?

421
00:44:05,893 --> 00:44:11,357
I ask nothing for myself.
Only peace in my old age.

422
00:44:11,732 --> 00:44:14,860
But I must please the world around me.

423
00:44:16,696 --> 00:44:22,535
Michael, your father was
a reasonable man. Learn from him.

424
00:44:25,454 --> 00:44:28,624
I learned many things from my father.

425
00:44:34,171 --> 00:44:39,844
Call a meeting, my friend,
so there are no debts or grudges.

426
00:44:40,886 --> 00:44:43,681
We will make the peace, you and I.

427
00:45:01,073 --> 00:45:03,659
The Vatican announced today...

428
00:45:03,743 --> 00:45:07,580
that Pope Paul VI has canceled
his Sunday blessing...

429
00:45:07,663 --> 00:45:09,582
due to ill health.

430
00:45:09,665 --> 00:45:12,835
His physician has ordered
total bedrest...

431
00:45:12,918 --> 00:45:15,838
and cessation of all activities.

432
00:45:23,804 --> 00:45:25,723
They've had a press conference.

433
00:45:25,848 --> 00:45:28,934
The Pope's condition
is grave. "Gravissimo."

434
00:45:57,713 --> 00:46:01,258
The purpose of this meeting
is to ratify...

435
00:46:01,592 --> 00:46:04,929
the motion passed by our
shareholders in New York.

436
00:46:06,847 --> 00:46:07,973
Please...

437
00:46:09,016 --> 00:46:13,771
Our group represents a consortium
of Catholic businessmen

438
00:46:13,854 --> 00:46:16,691
against the Corleone control.

439
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:19,777
The Vatican has cast its vote.

440
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:22,279
Corleone Group
already controls the Board.

441
00:46:22,822 --> 00:46:27,618
According to the Lateran Treaty, the
Vatican vote must be ratified here.

442
00:46:27,702 --> 00:46:29,870
Here in Rome, by the Pope.

443
00:46:33,791 --> 00:46:36,669
The Pope is gravely ill.

444
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:41,757
Until he recovers, I am powerless.

445
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:45,928
- What if he dies?
- Then...

446
00:46:46,929 --> 00:46:50,141
...as you Americans say,
all bets are off.

447
00:46:50,641 --> 00:46:52,518
Gentlemen, please.

448
00:46:53,811 --> 00:46:57,231
This is a brief delay. Nothing more.

449
00:47:02,361 --> 00:47:04,697
Your Excellency, gentlemen...

450
00:47:05,781 --> 00:47:11,036
I advise you to join us in our prayers
for the Holy Father's recovery.

451
00:47:12,621 --> 00:47:14,373
We had an agreement!

452
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:19,503
This meeting was to be
merely a formality.

453
00:47:19,587 --> 00:47:24,925
- Please sit down.
- I'd rather stand. Give me an answer.

454
00:47:25,009 --> 00:47:30,514
The Immobiliare has its roots in the
European tradition. Please understand.

455
00:47:31,390 --> 00:47:34,643
I understand.
Your tactics are despicable.

456
00:47:34,727 --> 00:47:37,897
That's quite an indictment,
coming from a Corleone.

457
00:47:37,980 --> 00:47:42,359
- Gentlemen, gentlemen!
- Remember you are in the Vatican.

458
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:51,869
- What is it that you want?
- Yes, you will take control.

459
00:47:53,037 --> 00:47:56,582
We'll gladly put you at the helm
of our little fleet,

460
00:47:57,082 --> 00:48:00,878
but our ships must all sail
in the same direction.

461
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:08,052
Otherwise, who can say how long
your stay with us will last?

462
00:48:10,304 --> 00:48:16,143
It's not personal. It's only business.
You should know, Godfather.

463
00:48:20,189 --> 00:48:21,607
Very well.

464
00:48:22,858 --> 00:48:27,780
You want to do business with me?
I will do business with you.

465
00:48:28,823 --> 00:48:30,741
Vipers, all of them.

466
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:39,959
- We're back with the Borgias!
- Uncle Michael...

467
00:48:40,042 --> 00:48:43,420
- Andrew!
- I heard you were here.

468
00:48:43,504 --> 00:48:46,966
It's so nice to see you.
Vincent, it's so nice.

469
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:51,262
What is this about the Borgias?
Those days are over.

470
00:48:56,725 --> 00:48:58,602
- Recognize it?
- Yeah.

471
00:49:00,396 --> 00:49:05,067
Genco Olive Oil. That's where our
grandfather started as a delivery boy.

472
00:49:06,527 --> 00:49:08,737
Three years later he owned it.

473
00:49:08,821 --> 00:49:11,115
- Only in America.
- That's it.

474
00:49:12,157 --> 00:49:17,329
Vincenzo, where have you been hiding?
We need your help so badly.

475
00:49:17,413 --> 00:49:19,039
What can I do for you?

476
00:49:19,123 --> 00:49:21,292
Get rid of Joe Zasa. He sells drugs...

477
00:49:21,375 --> 00:49:26,297
Now that I'm an older woman,
I'm afraid to go out at night.

478
00:49:26,380 --> 00:49:28,757
Where should they be now?

479
00:49:28,841 --> 00:49:31,927
- Lou, what's going on?
- We're late.

480
00:49:33,888 --> 00:49:36,682
- Have I ever let you down?
- I trust you.

481
00:49:36,765 --> 00:49:39,018
- Don't worry.
- Thank you.

482
00:49:39,101 --> 00:49:40,769
Enjoy yourselves.

483
00:49:47,651 --> 00:49:51,363
- What was that?
- The neighborhood's in trouble.

484
00:49:52,489 --> 00:49:55,242
- Do you keep an eye out for them?
- Yes.

485
00:49:55,326 --> 00:49:57,870
- And for me?
- From now on.

486
00:49:59,121 --> 00:50:03,125
- I've missed you all this time.
- I missed you too, cousin.

487
00:50:03,208 --> 00:50:06,128
I missed growing up with my cousins.

488
00:50:06,211 --> 00:50:08,672
