But I never doubted his love.

734
01:16:38,844 --> 01:16:43,557
He would do anything for me.
But his temper...

735
01:16:46,894 --> 01:16:50,856
Too much. It clouded his reason.

736
01:16:52,358 --> 01:16:54,944
I don't want you to make that mistake.

737
01:16:57,738 --> 01:16:59,031
Also...

738
01:17:00,324 --> 01:17:02,910
...he, too, had a way with women.

739
01:17:04,828 --> 01:17:07,289
- Vincent...
- So I hear.

740
01:17:07,373 --> 01:17:09,708
What are you doing with my daughter?

741
01:17:12,586 --> 01:17:14,755
What are you doing with her?

742
01:17:19,093 --> 01:17:21,011
It's too dangerous.

743
01:17:24,098 --> 01:17:25,766
Do you hear me?

744
01:17:31,855 --> 01:17:33,065
Okay.

745
01:17:47,496 --> 01:17:48,998
Vincenzo...

746
01:17:53,127 --> 01:17:57,006
When they come,
they'll come at what you love.

747
01:18:05,764 --> 01:18:08,308
Michael, you must lead another life.

748
01:18:09,184 --> 01:18:14,231
You have everything a man could
desire. It's time for you to retire.

749
01:18:15,607 --> 01:18:17,943
I have too much responsibility.

750
01:18:19,361 --> 01:18:24,950
Immobiliare? It's too difficult now.
You should really get out.

751
01:18:25,034 --> 01:18:29,747
What do you know
about those pezzi da novanta in Italy?

752
01:18:33,751 --> 01:18:37,171
I'm too old to know anything
about those new people.

753
01:18:37,713 --> 01:18:41,842
I must accept my age
and grow my olives and tomatoes.

754
01:18:43,677 --> 01:18:47,056
- We're not that old.
- But you're very ill.

755
01:18:48,307 --> 01:18:52,352
Michael... Let me see
what can be done.

756
01:18:53,520 --> 01:18:56,648
Let me work to make your path
a little easier.

757
01:18:57,900 --> 01:19:02,946
- Your friendship does that always.
- That makes me happy.

758
01:19:03,655 --> 01:19:07,826
Joey Zasa...
You were wrong about him.

759
01:19:08,994 --> 01:19:12,372
I trust too much.
That's always been my fault.

760
01:19:20,214 --> 01:19:23,842
Michael... treachery is everywhere.

761
01:19:24,426 --> 01:19:28,055
You still have your fingers
on the strings, even now.

762
01:19:29,932 --> 01:19:32,226
Let's see more of each other.

763
01:19:32,935 --> 01:19:37,356
- Michael, in Sicily?
- In Sicily.

764
01:19:38,315 --> 01:19:40,150
In Sicilia.

765
01:19:40,984 --> 01:19:42,361
In Sicilia.

766
01:20:30,617 --> 01:20:32,161
How are you?

767
01:20:32,953 --> 01:20:35,747
Don Bendino, my old friend.

768
01:21:07,112 --> 01:21:12,159
I brought you here, so that my old
friend and protector, Don Tommasino,

769
01:21:12,784 --> 01:21:14,328
could advise us.

770
01:21:16,163 --> 01:21:18,999
What do you think about Altobello?

771
01:21:20,209 --> 01:21:23,128
A very talented man.

772
01:21:23,503 --> 01:21:27,466
He has kept the peace between our
Sicilian and American friends.

773
01:21:28,342 --> 01:21:30,761
The saint of reason.

774
01:21:32,804 --> 01:21:36,600
A blood bath in Atlantic City
left New York a mess.

775
01:21:37,809 --> 01:21:40,270
Joey Zasa at least was running
a tight ship,

776
01:21:40,354 --> 01:21:44,191
but with him out of the picture
we must step in.

777
01:21:44,274 --> 01:21:48,070
- Step back in...
- Or the Chinese and Colombians will.

778
01:21:48,987 --> 01:21:53,867
The Corleones left drugs, so New York
is weak, and Palermo is strong.

779
01:21:55,285 --> 01:21:59,373
Your enemies always get strong
on what you leave behind.

780
01:22:02,042 --> 01:22:06,421
Who could give the order
for that massacre...

781
01:22:08,465 --> 01:22:12,219
and still pressure the Vatican deal?

782
01:22:12,386 --> 01:22:17,641
Only Lucchesi can reach
between these two worlds.

783
01:22:19,893 --> 01:22:23,188
"Our ships must all sail
in the same direction"...

784
01:22:24,982 --> 01:22:28,318
Italian politics have had these men
for centuries.

785
01:22:28,402 --> 01:22:30,821
They are the true Mafia.

786
01:22:30,904 --> 01:22:34,283
The Archbishop and the Vatican Bank,
that's the big problem.

787
01:22:34,366 --> 01:22:38,287
They're the same problem.
B.J., they're connected.

788
01:22:39,204 --> 01:22:41,915
The Archbishop has powerful friends.

789
01:22:44,626 --> 01:22:46,128
They totally protect him.

790
01:22:46,420 --> 01:22:51,008
Is there someone in the
Church we can turn to?

791
01:22:51,174 --> 01:22:54,594
Someone we can tell
our problem to?

792
01:22:56,054 --> 01:22:58,056
Cardinal Lamberto.

793
01:22:58,307 --> 01:23:03,478
A wise and good man...
very influential.

794
01:23:03,979 --> 01:23:07,232
He will see you.

795
01:23:12,321 --> 01:23:17,784
I will see this Cardinal Lamberto
and see if we can work things out.

796
01:23:19,578 --> 01:23:24,082
You honor your agreements,
but you are dealing with crooks.

797
01:23:25,250 --> 01:23:27,252
They have no honor.

798
01:23:29,171 --> 01:23:31,006
My word is final.

799
01:23:41,975 --> 01:23:46,188
Politics and crime,
they're the same thing.

800
01:24:08,335 --> 01:24:14,883
I've invited you all here to celebrate
my son's debut in an opera house...

801
01:24:15,425 --> 01:24:17,344
We'll play "Philadelphia".

802
01:24:18,804 --> 01:24:23,100
Seven cards. Two down, four up.
Deuces and one-eyed jacks are wild.

803
01:24:23,183 --> 01:24:25,685
...in the opera
"Cavallaria Rusticana".

804
01:24:25,769 --> 01:24:30,232
- It's "Cavalleria Rusticana, " Dad.
- "Cavalleria."

805
01:24:30,315 --> 01:24:32,818
I think I have tickets
to the wrong opera.

806
01:24:32,901 --> 01:24:34,986
I've been in New York too long.

807
01:24:35,862 --> 01:24:39,324
You will all receive tickets,
so come on time.

808
01:24:39,408 --> 01:24:41,618
Dad, I've got a present for you.

809
01:24:45,497 --> 01:24:49,626
It comes from the town of Corleone
and it's authentic Sicilian.

810
01:24:50,877 --> 01:24:53,964
And... I learned it for you.

811
01:26:23,887 --> 01:26:29,142
She was wonderful, beautiful.
I loved her. And then she died

812
01:26:30,602 --> 01:26:35,524
My trusted bodyguard
planted a bomb in my car.

813
01:26:37,442 --> 01:26:39,444
She drove it before I did.

814
01:26:41,112 --> 01:26:44,199
Why is such a beautiful country
so violent?

815
01:26:44,616 --> 01:26:46,409
History.

816
01:26:46,493 --> 01:26:50,789
Mom was telling me about when your
biggest worry was passing your exams.

817
01:26:51,081 --> 01:26:54,417
- Yes, it was then.
- I worry about you now.

818
01:26:54,960 --> 01:26:59,798
Mary, you're such a
warm-hearted girl. You always were.

819
01:27:00,465 --> 01:27:03,760
- I love my family.
- Even your cousin Vincent?

820
01:27:05,095 --> 01:27:06,972
I really love him.

821
01:27:08,056 --> 01:27:11,017
- He's your first cousin.
- Then I love him first.

822
01:27:12,143 --> 01:27:14,854
Mary, you can't see him.

823
01:27:20,151 --> 01:27:24,656
- Please, promise me.
- No!

824
01:27:25,365 --> 01:27:28,660
Mary, listen to me.
You can't see him anymore.

825
01:27:28,785 --> 01:27:30,662
- Not in that fashion.
- No.

826
01:27:31,162 --> 01:27:33,248
- Obey me on this.
- No, Dad!

827
01:27:38,712 --> 01:27:42,716
Mary is smart, Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

828
01:28:05,989 --> 01:28:08,658
Bella cugina... Tesoro mio.

829
01:28:20,170 --> 01:28:22,547
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

830
01:28:23,506 --> 01:28:26,843
I want you to do something for me.
It's dangerous.

831
01:28:28,637 --> 01:28:31,931
Good. I'm in. What do you need?

832
01:28:32,724 --> 01:28:35,852
I want you to sell your soul
to Don Altobello.

833
01:28:36,561 --> 01:28:38,146
To betray me.

834
01:28:41,650 --> 01:28:43,610
He'd never believe me.

835
01:28:44,736 --> 01:28:46,946
- That depends.
- Sit down.

836
01:28:49,824 --> 01:28:51,493
I have an idea.

837
01:28:53,161 --> 01:28:56,665
See if you can learn
how high Altobello is connected.

838
01:29:01,002 --> 01:29:02,712
Arrange a meeting.

839
01:29:05,298 --> 01:29:09,844
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

840
01:29:11,012 --> 01:29:13,973
- Ask for his help.
- What problems?

841
01:29:16,017 --> 01:29:18,853
That you want to run away
with my daughter.

842
01:29:19,604 --> 01:29:23,024
But you know that if you do,
I will become your enemy.

843
01:29:28,279 --> 01:29:31,658
- You know that I would never do that.
- I know.

844
01:29:32,867 --> 01:29:37,372
Ask Altobello to speak to me.
To further the marriage.

845
01:29:38,081 --> 01:29:42,919
But you're cousins, after all. Michael
was always a little old-fashioned.

846
01:29:44,170 --> 01:29:49,008
Say you can't belong to my legitimate
world. That you want your own family.

847
01:29:50,009 --> 01:29:53,138
I could straighten out
what Joey Zasa left behind.

848
01:29:54,889 --> 01:29:57,851
If you could use your friendship
to persuade him,

849
01:29:58,893 --> 01:30:01,771
I would be indebted to you forever.

850
01:30:03,732 --> 01:30:07,277
A Corleone knows the value
of such a friend.

851
01:30:09,028 --> 01:30:11,573
Then you would work for me?

852
01:30:12,407 --> 01:30:13,658
Sì.

853
01:30:16,286 --> 01:30:18,872
Bacio la mano, Don Altobello.

854
01:30:21,958 --> 01:30:27,005
If he hints that he wants you
to betray me, get insulted,

855
01:30:27,756 --> 01:30:29,841
because that's his trap.

856
01:30:36,473 --> 01:30:39,684
You're not telling me
the whole truth, Vincenzo.

857
01:30:42,979 --> 01:30:48,568
Isn't it true, that with Michael gone,
the girl controls everything?

858
01:30:52,906 --> 01:30:56,618
- Leave the girl out of this.
- Of course, you love her.

859
01:30:56,701 --> 01:30:58,369
And she loves you.

860
01:31:18,932 --> 01:31:22,101
I guessed it, didn't I?

861
01:31:23,728 --> 01:31:28,525
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.
I'll be learning a lot from you.

862
01:31:29,609 --> 01:31:33,238
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

863
01:31:35,657 --> 01:31:38,368
It's my duty
to make the introductions.

864
01:31:45,208 --> 01:31:47,335
Don Lucchesi.

865
01:31:49,921 --> 01:31:55,552
Don Altobello tells me that you have
a strong character. A man of respect.

866
01:31:55,635 --> 01:31:58,847
This is the hero who put
Joey Zasa in his grave.

867
01:31:59,514 --> 01:32:03,351
If we'd known of his existence,
we wouldn't have backed Joey.

868
01:32:03,852 --> 01:32:05,937
No one wants another Joe.

869
01:32:07,856 --> 01:32:10,024
Let me be your friend.

870
01:32:10,650 --> 01:32:14,821
- Even the strongest man needs friends.
- I'm flattered.

871
01:32:16,072 --> 01:32:20,743
You're a man of finance and politics.
Things I don't understand.

872
01:32:22,412 --> 01:32:26,332
You understand guns.
Finance is a gun.

873
01:32:27,542 --> 01:32:31,838
Politics is knowing
when to pull the trigger.

874
01:32:36,259 --> 01:32:37,468
How can I help?

875
01:32:38,720 --> 01:32:39,929
Vieni?

876
01:32:43,016 --> 01:32:48,354
Blessed is the peacemaker,
for he can be called the child of God.

877
01:32:48,813 --> 01:32:51,566
- Tuparli Italiano un poco?
- Sì.

878
01:33:15,882 --> 01:33:18,676
The wheelchair, for Don Tommasino.

879
01:33:26,476 --> 01:33:31,272
I trusted this business arrangement
with the Archbishop. I trusted him.

880
01:33:31,356 --> 01:33:34,567
I was sure his honesty
was beyond a doubt.

881
01:33:35,568 --> 01:33:39,864
But, as you see,
I'm now the victim of a swindle.

882
01:33:40,615 --> 01:33:42,617
He's stalling me.

883
01:33:42,700 --> 01:33:46,704
Vast monies have gone to
people in high political places

884
01:33:46,788 --> 01:33:49,749
and the Vatican Bank is the guarantor.

885
01:33:49,832 --> 01:33:54,837
If what you say is true,
there will be a great scandal.

886
01:33:57,048 --> 01:34:02,095
Look at this stone. It has been
in the water for a very long time,

887
01:34:02,178 --> 01:34:05,890
but the water has not penetrated it.

888
01:34:10,144 --> 01:34:11,521
Look...

889
01:34:12,647 --> 01:34:17,819
Perfectly dry. The same thing
has happened to men in Europe.

890
01:34:17,902 --> 01:34:21,823
For centuries they have been
surrounded by Christianity,

891
01:34:22,865 --> 01:34:28,705
but Christ has not penetrated.
Christ doesn't live within them.

892
01:34:32,834 --> 01:34:36,838
- What's happening?
- Could you get me something sweet?

893
01:34:36,921 --> 01:34:40,341
Some orange juice, candy...

894
01:34:44,012 --> 01:34:46,347
I have trouble with diabetes.

895
01:34:49,976 --> 01:34:52,395
My blood sugar goes low.

896
01:34:52,478 --> 01:34:54,230
I understand.

897
01:35:17,587 --> 01:35:20,465
It happens sometimes
when I'm under stress.

898
01:35:21,340 --> 01:35:22,842
I understand.

899
01:35:24,969 --> 01:35:28,848
To come to you
on such a delicate matter...

900
01:35:31,726 --> 01:35:36,147
Accusations against your Archbishop.
It was difficult for me.

901
01:35:37,857 --> 01:35:39,776
The mind suffers

902
01:35:40,151 --> 01:35:42,904
and the body cries out.

903
01:35:49,077 --> 01:35:50,745
That's true.

904
01:35:52,330 --> 01:35:56,042
Would you like to make
your confession?

905
01:36:03,007 --> 01:36:04,842
Your Eminence, I'm...

906
01:36:09,013 --> 01:36:14,519
It's been so long. I wouldn't...
I wouldn't know where to...

907
01:36:15,978 --> 01:36:17,814
It's been 30 years.

908
01:36:19,899 --> 01:36:22,527
I'd use up too much of your time,
I think.

909
01:36:23,444 --> 01:36:25,947
I always have time to save souls.

910
01:36:27,657 --> 01:36:32,203
- Well, I'm beyond redemption.
- No, no...

911
01:36:41,629 --> 01:36:45,299
I hear the confessions
of my own priests here.

912
01:36:46,717 --> 01:36:50,138
Sometimes the desire to confess
is overwhelming,

913
01:36:51,013 --> 01:36:53,224
and we must seize the moment.

914
01:36:58,062 --> 01:37:01,649
What is the point of confessing
if I don't repent?

915
01:37:04,110 --> 01:37:06,612
I hear you are a practical man.

916
01:37:07,530 --> 01:37:09,615
What have you got to lose?

917
01:37:21,419 --> 01:37:22,879
Go on.

918
01:37:29,594 --> 01:37:30,803
I...

919
01:37:32,096 --> 01:37:34,098
...betrayed my wife.

920
01:37:35,850 --> 01:37:37,310
Go on, my son.

921
01:37:42,899 --> 01:37:44,859
I betrayed myself.

922
01:37:47,904 --> 01:37:49,322
I killed men.

923
01:37:53,451 --> 01:37:55,995
And I ordered men to be killed.

924
01:37:57,413 --> 01:37:59,498
Go on, my son. Go on.

925
01:38:05,379 --> 01:38:06,839
It's useless.

926
01:38:08,883 --> 01:38:10,468
Go on, my son.

927
01:38:12,011 --> 01:38:13,346
I killed...

928
01:38:18,476 --> 01:38:21,103
I ordered the death of my brother.

929
01:38:22,063 --> 01:38:24,023
He injured me.

930
01:38:25,566 --> 01:38:27,652
I killed my mother's son.

931
01:38:29,445 --> 01:38:31,530
I killed my father's son.

932
01:38:42,208 --> 01:38:46,712
Your sins are terrible,
and it is just that you suffer.

933
01:38:48,214 --> 01:38:50,716
Your life could be redeemed,

934
01:38:51,968 --> 01:38:56,013
but I know that you don't
believe that. You will not change.

935
01:39:19,578 --> 01:39:24,458
Pope Paul VI, Supreme Pontiff
of the Roman Catholic Church.

936
01:39:24,625 --> 01:39:28,087
Died last night at 9:40 p.m.

937
01:39:28,796 --> 01:39:32,008
The Pope was 81 years old,

938
01:39:32,758 --> 01:39:38,431
and had been in poor health
for the last several months.

939
01:39:48,024 --> 01:39:49,483
Connie...

940
01:39:51,277 --> 01:39:55,781
All my life I've kept trying
to go up in society.

941
01:39:56,407 --> 01:39:59,285
To where everything higher up
was legal, straight...

942
01:40:01,412 --> 01:40:04,999
But the higher I go,
the more crooked it becomes.

943
01:40:07,710 --> 01:40:09,920
Where the hell does it end?

944
01:40:18,929 --> 01:40:22,224
They've been killing each other
for centuries here.

945
01:40:23,768 --> 01:40:27,855
For money, for pride, for family.

946
01:40:31,108 --> 01:40:35,112
To keep from becoming the slaves
of the rich pezzi da novanta.

947
01:40:42,244 --> 01:40:44,288
I made confession, Connie.

948
01:40:45,289 --> 01:40:47,375
I confessed my sins.

949
01:40:49,210 --> 01:40:51,670
Why? That's not like you.

950
01:40:51,754 --> 01:40:54,548
You don't have to confess your sins
to a stranger.

951
01:40:55,216 --> 01:40:56,675
It was the man.

952
01:40:57,718 --> 01:41:01,347
He's a good man. A true priest.

953
01:41:05,559 --> 01:41:07,645
He can change things.

954
01:41:09,939 --> 01:41:11,607
Michael...

955
01:41:13,192 --> 01:41:17,071
You know,
sometimes I think of poor Fredo.

956
01:41:17,863 --> 01:41:21,200
Drowned. It was God's will.

957
01:41:23,661 --> 01:41:25,913
It was a terrible accident.

958
01:41:27,206 --> 01:41:29,125
But it's finished.

959
01:41:34,171 --> 01:41:36,215
Michael, I love you.

960
01:41:38,467 --> 01:41:40,386
I'll always help you.

961
01:41:52,731 --> 01:41:54,150
Connie...

962
01:42:24,305 --> 01:42:31,312
I am honored, Don Altobello, that
you've come from Palermo to visit me.

963
01:42:34,482 --> 01:42:39,487
Hey, the little kid! He's grown.

964
01:42:40,237 --> 01:42:42,031
Do the donkey for me.

965
01:42:59,507 --> 01:43:03,594
It's been some time since we
did business together.

966
01:43:07,556 --> 01:43:12,561
You are my "ace in the hole,"
as we say in America.

967
01:43:12,645 --> 01:43:18,484
I have a stone in my shoe.
You can remove it.

968
01:43:25,824 --> 01:43:28,702
Only one stone?

969
01:43:30,746 --> 01:43:36,669
It's dangerous. A famous man.

970
01:43:36,752 --> 01:43:40,089
You will have to take precautions.

971
01:43:43,384 --> 01:43:48,722
Tell me what to do.
Then I will tell you my price.

972
01:43:53,018 --> 01:43:55,729
What bread!

973
01:43:59,775 --> 01:44:03,946
Olive oil...

974
01:44:07,199 --> 01:44:10,536
Virgin... only in Sicily.

975
01:44:13,038 --> 01:44:14,373
Alla salute!

976
01:44:14,456 --> 01:44:17,543
To death.

977
01:44:30,806 --> 01:44:32,308
Kay!

978
01:44:32,391 --> 01:44:34,810
- Connie!
- How are you?

979
01:44:34,893 --> 01:44:37,980
Mary, I've missed you.

980
01:44:38,397 --> 01:44:42,276
- Hello, Michael.
- Mom, look at this.

981
01:44:46,363 --> 01:44:48,782
It's too bad Douglas couldn't come.

982
01:44:48,866 --> 01:44:52,286
I know.
He had a very important trial.

983
01:44:52,369 --> 01:44:54,413
I know he wanted to come.

984
01:44:55,372 --> 01:44:57,416
- The car is...
- Okay.

985
01:44:59,376 --> 01:45:05,591
- Well, your son is an artist.
- Yes. Thanks to you.

986
01:45:06,425 --> 01:45:10,596
- What for?
- For making me let him go.

987
01:45:11,472 --> 01:45:16,310
Well, after all these years, here I am
in Sicily for the first time.

988
01:45:16,393 --> 01:45:18,604
I want to get
a picture of you together.

989
01:45:18,687 --> 01:45:19,813
Okay.

990
01:45:21,523 --> 01:45:23,484
Hey, Dad. Smile!

991
01:45:27,863 --> 01:45:30,699
I see you still have Al Neri. Why?

992
01:45:32,034 --> 01:45:35,537
I need him. He helps me
get in and out of the car.

993
01:45:36,747 --> 01:45:40,417
- He carries my briefcase.
- You're still a liar, Michael.

994
01:45:41,752 --> 01:45:45,089
Let me show you Sicily,
the real Sicily.

995
01:45:45,172 --> 01:45:48,092
So you'll understand
the family history.

996
01:45:48,175 --> 01:45:50,969
I think I understand it well enough.

997
01:47:00,539 --> 01:47:03,375
- Are they as good as they look?
- Better.

998
01:47:03,459 --> 01:47:08,005
They're the best. As long as they are
around, Uncle Michael is safe.

999
01:47:08,505 --> 01:47:10,007
Goodbye.

1000
01:47:12,468 --> 01:47:14,595
Tell your father
I'll be back for dinner.

1001
01:47:14,678 --> 01:47:15,679
Okay.

1002
01:47:16,388 --> 01:47:18,932
- Have fun.
- Tell Tony to wait for me.

1003
01:47:19,016 --> 01:47:20,601
I will.

1004
01:47:22,978 --> 01:47:26,732
Buongiorno, signora. At your service.

1005
01:47:30,694 --> 01:47:33,530
If I see Dad, I'll tell him you left.

1006
01:47:39,161 --> 01:47:42,748
You're the only one left
with my father's strength.

1007
01:47:45,042 --> 01:47:48,921
If anything happens to Michael,
I want you to strike back.

1008
01:47:51,840 --> 01:47:53,842
I'll have everything ready.

1009
01:47:56,428 --> 01:47:57,971
Do you swear?

1010
01:48:06,396 --> 01:48:08,148
I swear to you.

1011
01:48:31,463 --> 01:48:33,465
You know Mary's in love.

1012
01:48:34,842 --> 01:48:36,635
Yes, I know.

1013
01:48:37,636 --> 01:48:41,682
With a handsome young Italian man
with dark eyes...

1014
01:48:43,016 --> 01:48:44,810
I won't allow it.

1015
01:48:47,813 --> 01:48:51,441
It's wrong.
It's wrong and it's dangerous.

1016
01:48:51,942 --> 01:48:54,820
"Father, my father!"

1017
01:48:55,279 --> 01:48:57,781
"Give me some time to pray
to the Lord."

1018
01:48:58,824 --> 01:49:01,660
The Baroness of Carini had
betrayed her husband...

1019
01:49:02,411 --> 01:49:05,122
and fallen in love with her cousin.

1020
01:49:05,581 --> 01:49:07,624
"There will be no forgiveness!"

1021
01:49:07,708 --> 01:49:11,169
Her father stabbed her through
the heart.

1022
01:49:23,849 --> 01:49:25,183
Honor?

1023
01:49:26,810 --> 01:49:29,187
Would it help any if I said
they were only puppets?

1024
01:49:44,745 --> 01:49:47,748
I remember the time you came
to my parents' house

1025
01:49:47,831 --> 01:49:51,585
and told me about the family business.

1026
01:49:51,668 --> 01:49:56,673
How you'd never have anything
to do with it. You sounded like Tony.

1027
01:49:57,758 --> 01:49:59,760
I was a lot like Tony.

1028
01:50:08,310 --> 01:50:11,355
Father, where are you going?

1029
01:50:21,740 --> 01:50:26,036
I know you. You're Mosca
of Montelepre.

1030
01:50:26,995 --> 01:50:30,791
You were an assassin then
and you're an assassin now.

1031
01:50:31,124 --> 01:50:34,544
I know Michael Corleone
is at your house.

1032
01:50:34,753 --> 01:50:36,797
I will pass through the gates
with you.

1033
01:50:54,022 --> 01:50:55,774
How are you?

1034
01:50:55,857 --> 01:50:59,361
This is Calo, one of my bodyguards
in the old days.

1035
01:51:05,117 --> 01:51:07,869
- We can wait here.
- You want a drink?

1036
01:51:13,458 --> 01:51:16,294
I spent a lot of time in this room...

1037
01:51:17,421 --> 01:51:19,464
...thinking of you.

1038
01:51:22,467 --> 01:51:24,678
And then you got married.

1039
01:51:28,140 --> 01:51:31,643
- I still thought of you.
- What's in that room?

1040
01:51:36,398 --> 01:51:40,068
This is dangerous for you.
This is Sicily.

1041
01:51:43,113 --> 01:51:45,407
- I love this country.
- Why?

1042
01:51:48,034 --> 01:51:51,246
Well, all through history,

1043
01:51:51,329 --> 01:51:54,040
terrible things
have happened to these people.

1044
01:51:54,958 --> 01:51:57,252
Terrible injustices.

1045
01:51:58,211 --> 01:52:03,049
But they still expect good,
rather than bad, will happen to them.

1046
01:52:03,508 --> 01:52:05,927
Sort of like me and you?

1047
01:52:09,765 --> 01:52:12,350
- How so?
- I'm still here, right?

1048
01:52:13,226 --> 01:52:14,519
We do have a bad history,

1049
01:52:15,395 --> 01:52:16,396
but I'm still here.

1050
01:52:16,480 --> 01:52:19,274
Yes, you are, but with dread.

1051
01:52:22,194 --> 01:52:23,737
Give me the order!

1052
01:52:26,031 --> 01:52:28,784
Is that supposed to make me
not dread you?

1053
01:52:31,745 --> 01:52:34,039
We're in Sicily. It's opera.

1054
01:52:36,541 --> 01:52:38,084
Okay.

1055
01:52:40,629 --> 01:52:42,339
What do we do now?

1056
01:52:45,258 --> 01:52:49,095
Be reasonable.
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1057
01:52:56,937 --> 01:52:58,980
I want you to forgive me.

1058
01:53:01,733 --> 01:53:04,653
- For what?
- Everything.

1059
01:53:08,281 --> 01:53:10,450
Like God?

1060
01:53:16,122 --> 01:53:19,167
I'm not the man that you think I am.

1061
01:53:21,461 --> 01:53:22,963
Michael, what do you want
from me?

1062
01:53:26,925 --> 01:53:28,593
I love you, Kay.

1063
01:53:30,512 --> 01:53:32,639
Don't dread me anymore.

1064
01:53:38,228 --> 01:53:42,482
You know,
every night here in Sicily...

1065
01:53:43,942 --> 01:53:50,031
...I dream about my wife
and my children...

1066
01:53:52,784 --> 01:53:54,953
...and how I lost them.

1067
01:54:01,543 --> 01:54:03,378
You know what, Michael...

1068
01:54:05,964 --> 01:54:08,258
I always loved you.

1069
01:54:12,804 --> 01:54:14,598
I always will.

1070
01:54:29,654 --> 01:54:31,531
What is it? What's wrong?

1071
01:54:32,866 --> 01:54:36,411
They found Don Tommasino shot.

1072
01:54:37,162 --> 01:54:38,580
Is he dead?

1073
01:54:41,249 --> 01:54:45,003
My master is dead.
Blood calls for blood.

1074
01:54:45,086 --> 01:54:48,381
I must have revenge!

1075
01:54:51,217 --> 01:54:57,474
Some day, you may have to do
a difficult service for me.

1076
01:54:57,557 --> 01:55:00,226
Command me.

1077
01:55:00,602 --> 01:55:01,770
It never ends.

1078
01:55:02,187 --> 01:55:03,688
I will avenge him!

1079
01:55:19,245 --> 01:55:20,830
Totals...

1080
01:55:22,832 --> 01:55:25,043
Lorscheider, 1 vote.

1081
01:55:25,877 --> 01:55:28,922
Siri, 11 votes.

1082
01:55:29,839 --> 01:55:33,218
Lamberto, 99 votes.

1083
01:55:38,515 --> 01:55:44,104
Do you accept your election
as supreme pontiff?

1084
01:55:44,187 --> 01:55:50,318
God, shed light on the decision
they have taken on my behalf.

1085
01:55:50,402 --> 01:55:52,529
I accept.

1086
01:55:52,612 --> 01:55:55,573
By what name do you
wish to be called?

1087
01:55:55,657 --> 01:55:58,785
John Paul the First.

1088
01:56:28,481 --> 01:56:34,696
I will do things "right away,"
rather than in "a little while"...

1089
01:56:35,155 --> 01:56:40,076
Frederick Keinszig, known as "God's
Banker", has been reported missing.

1090
01:56:40,785 --> 01:56:47,375
He was last seen leaving the Rome
offices of Vatican owned Immobiliare.

1091
01:56:48,209 --> 01:56:51,963
Also missing was a large sum
of money and several documents.

1092
01:56:53,298 --> 01:56:55,425
Keinszig, you fool.

1093
01:56:58,595 --> 01:57:03,683
His absence casts further suspicion
on the dealings of the Vatican Bank.

1094
01:57:03,767 --> 01:57:06,811
For several years,
the bank and its companies

1095
01:57:06,895 --> 01:57:10,148
have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practices.

1096
01:57:11,816 --> 01:57:16,446
Lucchesi, will you please
try to understand?

1097
01:57:17,572 --> 01:57:21,659
I have phoned him.
I have waited here by the phone.

1098
01:57:24,496 --> 01:57:28,333
You would do well to remember,
Mr. Lucchesi,

1099
01:57:29,542 --> 01:57:35,423
that this Pope has very different
ideas from the last one.

1100
01:57:57,695 --> 01:57:59,739
Goodbye, my old friend.

1101
01:58:02,367 --> 01:58:05,036
You could have lived a little longer.

1102
01:58:06,162 --> 01:58:08,540
I could be closer to my dream.

1103
01:58:14,963 --> 01:58:17,382
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1104
01:58:22,178 --> 01:58:26,057
Why was I so feared, and you so loved?

1105
01:58:27,100 --> 01:58:28,851
What was it?

1106
01:58:30,103 --> 01:58:32,105
I was no less honorable.

1107
01:58:34,232 --> 01:58:36,025
I wanted to do good.

1108
01:58:40,196 --> 01:58:43,116
What betrayed me? My mind? My heart?

1109
01:58:46,202 --> 01:58:48,746
Why do I condemn myself so?

1110
01:58:55,211 --> 01:58:57,130
I swear,

1111
01:58:57,422 --> 01:58:59,757
on the lives of my children...

1112
01:59:04,178 --> 01:59:07,015
Give me a chance to redeem myself...

1113
01:59:10,977 --> 01:59:14,522
...and I will sin no more.

1114
01:59:38,796 --> 01:59:42,675
You look pale. Bad news?
Tell me right away.

1115
01:59:44,844 --> 01:59:47,180
It's not just a bad banking deal.

1116
01:59:48,222 --> 01:59:50,350
These guys are butchers.

1117
01:59:51,601 --> 01:59:54,187
- What guys?
- Lucchesi.

1118
01:59:56,230 --> 02:00:00,068
He controls all of them:
Altobello, the Archbishop...

1119
02:00:01,819 --> 02:00:04,405
...others higher up, P2 maybe.

1120
02:00:04,489 --> 02:00:07,575
Secret unknown.
They're running things.

1121
02:00:11,287 --> 02:00:16,292
- I'm in their way.
- He's hired an assassin to kill you.

1122
02:00:16,834 --> 02:00:19,379
A Sicilian. I don't know his name.

1123
02:00:21,547 --> 02:00:23,758
But they say he never fails.

1124
02:00:25,093 --> 02:00:27,261
Then no one is safe.

1125
02:00:30,056 --> 02:00:32,266
Even the new Pope is in danger.

1126
02:00:33,351 --> 02:00:36,479
We still have time.
We can prevent this.

1127
02:00:41,984 --> 02:00:44,153
I tried, Vincent.

1128
02:00:46,364 --> 02:00:47,990
I tried...

1129
02:00:49,158 --> 02:00:53,705
...to keep everything from coming
to this. But it's not possible.

1130
02:00:55,373 --> 02:00:57,083
Not in this world.

1131
02:00:58,584 --> 02:01:00,253
Give me the order.

1132
02:01:04,340 --> 02:01:06,509
You won't be able to go back.

1133
02:01:07,552 --> 02:01:09,679
- You'll be like me.
- Good.

1134
02:01:11,389 --> 02:01:13,433
All my life I wanted out.

1135
02:01:14,308 --> 02:01:16,352
I wanted the family out.

1136
02:01:18,271 --> 02:01:20,189
I don't want out.

1137
02:01:20,648 --> 02:01:23,359
I want the power
to preserve the family.

1138
02:01:28,239 --> 02:01:30,283
I'm asking for the order.

1139
02:01:51,220 --> 02:01:53,014
It's done.

1140
02:01:54,348 --> 02:01:56,726
Because I can't do it anymore.

1141
02:02:01,022 --> 02:02:04,525
Well, it doesn't matter.
Vincent knows what to do.

1142
02:02:04,609 --> 02:02:09,614
Come on outside.
Take a rest and don't think about it.

1143
02:02:10,072 --> 02:02:12,950
- All I do is think about it.
- I'm your son.

1144
02:02:14,160 --> 02:02:16,329
Command me in all things.

1145
02:02:18,498 --> 02:02:20,374
Give up my daughter.

1146
02:02:23,461 --> 02:02:25,671
That's the price you pay...

1147
02:02:26,839 --> 02:02:29,008
...for the life you choose.

1148
02:02:55,284 --> 02:02:56,744
Nephew...

1149
02:02:59,288 --> 02:03:01,374
...from this moment on...

1150
02:03:02,625 --> 02:03:05,253
...call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1151
02:03:10,007 --> 02:03:11,300
Sit.

1152
02:03:26,315 --> 02:03:28,067
Don Vincenzo...

1153
02:03:34,073 --> 02:03:35,700
Don Corleone...

1154
02:03:39,328 --> 02:03:41,497
Don Vincenzo Corleone...

1155
02:05:15,216 --> 02:05:17,426
E tu, Vincenzo...

1156
02:05:17,510 --> 02:05:22,306
I know how you feel about Michael,
but you can't save him.

1157
02:05:23,182 --> 02:05:24,433
He's lost.

1158
02:05:26,060 --> 02:05:27,895
Think of yourself.

1159
02:05:29,063 --> 02:05:31,732
What's your answer, Vincent?

1160
02:05:33,359 --> 02:05:35,069
Enjoy the opera.

1161
02:05:37,154 --> 02:05:39,198
It's all taken care of.

1162
02:05:44,704 --> 02:05:47,456
Check the bar.
I'll check the top floor.

1163
02:05:51,127 --> 02:05:55,715
"Here's hoping Tony sings better at
the Teatro Massimo than in the shower.

1164
02:05:55,798 --> 02:05:58,134
"Love, Douglas."

1165
02:05:58,217 --> 02:06:01,470
- My darling Constanza!
- Don Altobello.

1166
02:06:02,596 --> 02:06:05,641
- This is a great occasion.
- Come, sit down.

1167
02:06:10,229 --> 02:06:14,525
Happy birthday. You're 80,
but don't look more than 60.

1168
02:06:14,608 --> 02:06:17,236
You're the only one who remembered.

1169
02:06:17,319 --> 02:06:18,946
We've just got the word.

1170
02:06:19,030 --> 02:06:22,575
The Pope has ratified
the Immobiliare deal. We've won.

1171
02:06:22,658 --> 02:06:24,285
Congratulations.

1172
02:06:27,079 --> 02:06:29,415
Strange how things work.

1173
02:06:29,498 --> 02:06:33,586
The Pope is doing what you
said he'd do. He's cleaning house.

1174
02:06:34,462 --> 02:06:38,466
He should be careful.
It's dangerous to be an honest man.

1175
02:06:44,513 --> 02:06:47,641
I want to put more muscle backstage
with Tony.

1176
02:06:59,695 --> 02:07:03,032
On your birthday you used to
shower me with treats.

1177
02:07:03,115 --> 02:07:04,950
Tootsie Rolls!

1178
02:07:05,785 --> 02:07:09,330
The nuns who made this cannoli
took a vow of silence.

1179
02:07:09,413 --> 02:07:11,290
They're the very finest.

1180
02:07:15,169 --> 02:07:17,880
- Hey.
- Hey, cous.

1181
02:07:19,924 --> 02:07:22,635
Hi. Where's your leather?

1182
02:07:26,847 --> 02:07:28,516
Stop it.

1183
02:07:34,480 --> 02:07:37,733
You're so thin. You eat it.

1184
02:07:54,333 --> 02:07:55,751
È buono.

1185
02:07:56,168 --> 02:07:58,504
Grazie!

1186
02:08:01,423 --> 02:08:05,761
It's over. There are things I have
to do that you can't be part of.

1187
02:08:05,845 --> 02:08:08,973
It's not your father's decision,
it's mine.

1188
02:08:10,683 --> 02:08:12,560
Don't hate your father.

1189
02:08:14,854 --> 02:08:18,649
There are things I'll be part of
that you can't be around.

1190
02:08:20,609 --> 02:08:23,279
After tonight,
you won't see me anymore.

1191
02:08:27,741 --> 02:08:31,287
You've got to understand, Mary.
You've got to understand.

1192
02:08:32,329 --> 02:08:33,873
I'll always love you.

1193
02:08:47,136 --> 02:08:48,929
Love somebody else.

1194
02:12:30,067 --> 02:12:34,029
- They won't try anything.
- Everything's fine. It's all clear.

1195
02:12:34,113 --> 02:12:36,907
I've already sent Al Neri
to the Vatican.

1196
02:12:49,503 --> 02:12:51,964
Mr. Lucchesi's house?

1197
02:12:52,047 --> 02:12:53,048
Yes.

1198
02:12:53,674 --> 02:12:57,928
I bring a message from
Michael Corleone.

1199
02:12:59,179 --> 02:13:00,681
Let him in.

1200
02:14:29,811 --> 02:14:31,688
Buona sera.

1201
02:17:52,681 --> 02:17:54,516
Good. You got him.

1202
02:18:46,818 --> 02:18:50,363
Tonight the Corleone family
settles its accounts.

1203
02:18:50,530 --> 02:18:55,202
Keinszig...
That little Swiss banker fuck.

1204
02:18:56,286 --> 02:19:00,248
He's been swindling everyone
from the beginning. Fuck him.

1205
02:19:02,000 --> 02:19:04,544
Don Lucchesi, my friend

1206
02:19:04,628 --> 02:19:07,214
Calo will pay him a visit at his home.

1207
02:19:10,050 --> 02:19:13,345
Neri, take a train to Rome.

1208
02:19:14,888 --> 02:19:17,349
Light a candle for the Archbishop.

1209
02:19:53,677 --> 02:19:55,846
Tea, Your Holiness? It will help
you sleep.

1210
02:20:18,994 --> 02:20:21,997
This is from Vincent Corleone.

1211
02:21:20,180 --> 02:21:21,806
It's serious.

1212
02:21:21,890 --> 02:21:25,352
Our man inside the Vatican
says there's a plot against the Pope.

1213
02:21:25,435 --> 02:21:27,479
He'll have a heart attack?

1214
02:21:34,444 --> 02:21:39,699
This Pope has powerful enemies.
We may not be in time to save him.

1215
02:21:42,661 --> 02:21:44,371
Let's go back.

1216
02:22:18,822 --> 02:22:20,365
Eminenza...

1217
02:22:36,214 --> 02:22:38,758
The Holy Father is dead!

1218
02:24:09,349 --> 02:24:10,683
Sleep.

1219
02:24:11,476 --> 02:24:13,436
Sleep, Godfather.

1220
02:24:28,952 --> 02:24:30,537
Our friend's dead.

1221
02:25:23,590 --> 02:25:25,675
Speak... tell me.

1222
02:25:26,968 --> 02:25:33,474
You have lost the
faith of the people.

1223
02:25:34,601 --> 02:25:39,230
He who builds on the people
builds on mud.

1224
02:25:39,772 --> 02:25:43,568
And Michael Corleone's message?

1225
02:26:00,168 --> 02:26:06,549
It's very important.
I must whisper it in your ear.

1226
02:26:10,553 --> 02:26:12,555
He's clean.

1227
02:26:30,907 --> 02:26:33,952
Power wears out those
who don't have it.

1228
02:28:02,623 --> 02:28:05,793
- I like this outfit.
- I figured you would.

1229
02:28:05,877 --> 02:28:07,754
Say hello.

1230
02:28:29,776 --> 02:28:33,696
- Can I talk to you now?
- No, it's not a good time.

1231
02:28:33,780 --> 02:28:37,492
- You're just like my father.
- Stay with the family. Go on.

1232
02:28:39,118 --> 02:28:41,037
- Talk to me.
- The twins are dead.

1233
02:28:41,120 --> 02:28:45,249
In about one minute, there will be
carabinieri all over this place.

1234
02:28:46,084 --> 02:28:48,961
Get everybody to the cars, quietly.

1235
02:28:49,045 --> 02:28:50,838
- Got it.
- Quiet.

1236
02:29:05,520 --> 02:29:08,689
The name Corleone
will be associated with a voice.

1237
02:29:18,408 --> 02:29:19,784
Dad...

1238
02:29:39,429 --> 02:29:43,182
Dad... Why are you doing this to me?

1239
02:29:52,442 --> 02:29:54,902
Move back, move back.

1240
02:29:56,362 --> 02:30:00,491
- You don't have to do this to me.
- Do what? What do you mean?

1241
02:30:26,851 --> 02:30:27,852
Dad...

1242
02:30:45,203 --> 02:30:47,163
No! Mary!

1243
02:30:50,500 --> 02:30:52,001
God, no!

